Privacy Policy and Notice of Collection of Personal Information
Humming Puppy Pty Ltd ("we," "us," "Humming Puppy") values your privacy. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your personal information when you use our website (https://hummingpuppy.uscreen.io) and mobile app.
1. Scope of This Privacy Policy
This policy applies to:
Users of our app and website
Clients or prospective clients
Suppliers or prospective suppliers
Independent contractors or applicants for such roles
Employees or job applicants (except where employee records are exempt under the Privacy Act)
It does not apply to third-party websites linked to Humming Puppy.
2. Consent
By using our app or engaging with us, you consent to our collection, use, and disclosure of your personal information in accordance with this policy.
3. What Personal Information We Collect
We may collect the following types of personal information:
Identity Data
: Name, date of birth, email, phone number, and address
Billing Data
: Payment details (processed via third-party payment providers)
Usage Data
: IP address, device information, browser type, and app usage patterns
Social Media Data
: Information shared via our social media channels
Employment Data
: For employees and applicants, we collect qualifications, health information, tax details, and performance records
4. How We Collect Personal Information
We collect data through:
Direct interactions: App usage, account sign-ups, purchases, customer inquiries
Forms: Registration, feedback, or contractual agreements
Social media: Engagement via platforms such as Instagram, Facebook, and LinkedIn
Third parties: Payment processors, analytics providers, credit agencies
Website and App analytics: Cookies, tracking technologies
5. How We Use Your Personal Information
We use your data to:
Provide and improve our app and services
Process payments and transactions
Respond to inquiries and customer support requests
Send promotional and marketing communications (you can opt out anytime)
Ensure compliance with legal and regulatory requirements
Manage employment-related matters
6. How We Share Your Personal Information
We do
not
sell or rent personal data. We may share information with:
Service Providers
: IT support, marketing agencies, payment processors
Business Partners
: If you engage with co-branded services
Legal Authorities
: When required by law
7. Data Retention and Deletion Policy
We retain personal data only as long as necessary to fulfill its intended purpose or legal obligations. You may request deletion of your data by contacting us at management@hummingpuppy.com. Some data may be retained as required by law.
8. Security Measures
We implement security measures to protect your data, including:
Encryption and secure password protocols
Access controls for authorized personnel only
Regular security audits and updates
Despite these measures, no online system is 100% secure. We encourage users to take precautions when sharing personal data.
9. Direct Marketing & Opt-Out
We may send promotional content. You can opt out by following the "unsubscribe" link in emails or contacting us directly.
10. Your Rights
You have the right to:
Access your personal information
Request corrections or updates
Withdraw consent for marketing communications
Request deletion of your data (subject to legal obligations)
To exercise these rights, contact us at management@hummingpuppy.com.
11. Complaints & Contact Information
For privacy concerns or complaints, contact our Privacy Officer at:
Email:
management@hummingpuppy.com
We will acknowledge your complaint within five business days and aim to resolve it within 30 days.
12. Changes to This Policy
We may update this policy periodically. Please review it regularly for changes. The latest version will always be available at
https://hummingpuppy.uscreen.io/pages/privacy-policy
.